<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-55-0378 </DOCNO><TEXT>This talk presents an overview of the equipment and methods being installedat Sandia National Laboratories, Albuquerque, to manage information ina digital form. To store and access this data, the Design InformationManagement Department is planning a network of Write-Once-Read-Many (WORM)optical disk storage, image management workstations in centralized locationsand across the laboratories, compression and conversion software, andaccess and database software interfaces to traditional engineering dataprocessing. Computer-aided design data will be transmitted directly tothe centralized storage area, and paper and microfilm documents willbe entered through scanning, which will allow drawing restoration, modification,and general editing.</TEXT></DOC>